<HTML>

<!-- FIRST make sure the critical fields are there -->
<?MIBLOCK COND=$(OR,$(NXST,$name),$(NXST,$full_name),$(NXST,$address))>
<center>
<big> Insufficient information: You must specify at least name, full_name, and address to make an entry</big>. Please go back and try again.
</center>
<?/MIBLOCK>

<!-- Looking good. Now just fix up the entries and create the record -->
<?MIBLOCK COND=$(AND,$(XST,$name),$(XST,$full_name),$(XST,$address))>

<TITLE>Confirmation: Added PERSON record</TITLE>

<!-- Double check input for apostrophes; fix em where found -->
<?MIVAR NAME=$name DELIMIT="'" REPLACE="''">$name<?/MIVAR>
<?MIVAR NAME=$full_name DELIMIT="'" REPLACE="''">$full_name<?/MIVAR>
<?MIVAR NAME=$address DELIMIT="'" REPLACE="''">$address<?/MIVAR>


<!- Make a new zdb_id for the record -->
<?MISQL SQL="execute function get_id('PERS');"><?/MISQL>
<?MIVAR NAME=$new_id>$1<?/MIVAR>

<!-- Great, now insert the record -->
<?MISQL SQL="insert into person (zdb_id, name, full_name, address,owner,entry_time) values ('$new_id','$name','$full_name','$address','$new_id',current);"><?/MISQL>

<h1 align=center>Confirmation</h1>

<big>Summary of action taken:</big><p>

Inserted one new person record with the following attributes:<br>
<?MIVAR>
<DL>
<DT> <b>Full name:</b>
<DD> $full_name
<DT> <b>MEDLINE name:</b>
<DD> $name
<DT> <b>Address:</b>
<DD> $address
<DT> <b>New record ID:</b>
<DD> $new_id
</DL>


<p>
You may now want to <A HREF="/cgi-bin_B/webdriver?MIval=aa-persview.apg&OID=$new_id">view the new PERSON record.</A> From there you can use the standard record updating mechanism to flesh out the remaining fields.
<?/MIVAR>

<?/MIBLOCK> <!-- ends cond name,address,etc exists -->

</HTML>